pwd = print current working directory
ls = list files & directories in the working directory
ls -l = list in long format
cd = change the working directory
cd .. = change the working directory to the parent
less = view test files
file = classify a file's contents
cp = copy files & directories
mv = move or rename files & directories
rm = remove files
rm -r = remove directories
rm -fr = force remove directories
mkdir = creat directories
> = redirect standard output to a file /overwrite from the begining/
>> = redirect standard output to a file /add new results to the end of the file/
< = redirect standard input from a file instead of the keyboard
Pipelines = the standard output of one command is fed into the standard input
            of another
* = matches any characters
e.g. 1
cp -u *.html destination
copy all HTML files from working directory to another
but only copy files that did not exist in the destination
or were newer than the versions in the destination directory
e.g. 2
rm *~
Delete all files in the current working directory that end with
the character "~"
